com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface NativeSignatureManager

public interface NativeSignatureManager

The NativeSignatureManager is the interface used to declare signatures of native methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:

decBehavior

NativeBehaviorSignature decBehavior(java.lang.String decExpr,
                                    java.lang.String[] importList)
Declares a native method signature defined in the specified expression string.

The expression string follows a special syntax mixing Java and C/C++.

Used ClassLoader, parameter importList using, spacing etc are the same as explained in NativeTypeManager.dec(String,String[]).

Syntax:

[static] [ReturnType] [callConv] [ClassName] [([param[,param]...])]
Where:

static : if declared the method is static.

ReturnType : the native variable type expression of the return.

callConv : method call convention, possible values are __stdcall and __cdecl (same literals and meaning as VisualC++). If not declared, the framework default is used (see getDefaultCallConv()).

ClassName : container Java native class of the method (or field). Only when a constructor or instance signature is declared.

param : native variable type expression of the parameter.

Cases:

1) Static methods:

static ReturnType [callConv] (...)
2) Constructors:
[callConv] ClassName(...)
3) Instance methods:
ReturnType [callConv] ClassName(...)

4) Static field-methods:

static ReturnType [callConv]
5) Instance field-methods:
static ReturnType [callConv] ClassName
Syntax of native variable types is explained in NativeTypeManager.dec(String,String[]).

Expression examples:

"static int [][]* __stdcall (int, java.lang.Boolean, java.lang.String[10], long [][]* , mypkg.MyClass[5])"

Declares a static method using the standard call convention.
"mypkg.MyClass[5]* mypkg.MyClass( int, double)"
Declares a instance method using the default call convention.
"mypkg.MyClass(int, double)"
Declares a constructor using the default call convention.
"static int __cdecl "
Declares a method to access a static field of int type using the C call convention.
"int __cdecl mypkg.MyClass"
Declares a method to access a instance field of int type of the native class mypkg.MyClass using the C call convention.

Parameters:
decExpr - the expression string defining the native signature.
importList - the included list of classes using Java import syntax. Can be null.
Returns:
the native signature of the declaration.
See Also:
NativeVarTypeManager.dec(String,String[]), NativeBehaviorSignature.getDeclarationString()

decConstructor

NativeConstructorSignature decConstructor(java.lang.Class clasz,
                                          java.lang.Object[] params,
                                          int callConv)
Declares a native constructor signature.

The constructor declaration needs the container class, the native variable types of the parameters and the call convention using the constants declared in CallConv.

Each element of the array params is a parameter declaration, index of the array is coincident with the corresponding index of the parameter starting in left. It is a native variable type declaration specified as:

  • A NativeParameterDec object.
  • A VarTypeNative object: the native parameter object is the result of calling to VarTypeNative.decParameter().
  • A Class object: the native variable type is the result of calling to NativeVarTypeManager.dec(Class).
  • A String object: the native variable type is the result of calling to NativeVarTypeManager.dec(String).

Parameters:
clasz - defines the container class of the constructor (and return type).
params - parameter list declaration.
callConv - call convention of the method.
Returns:
the native constructor signature.
See Also:
decBehavior(String)

decMethod

NativeMethodSignature decMethod(java.lang.Class clasz,
                                java.lang.Object returnType,
                                java.lang.Object[] params,
                                int callConv)
Declares a native method signature.

Current implementation is: 

 if (clasz == null)
     return decStaticMethod(returnType,params,callConv);
 else
     return decInstanceMethod(clasz,returnType,params,callConv);

Parameters:
clasz - defines the container class of the method. Can be null.
returnType - the return type declaration.
params - parameter list declaration.
callConv - call convention of the method.
Returns:
the native method signature.
See Also:
decBehavior(String), decStaticMethod(Object,Object[],int), decInstanceMethod(Class,Object,Object[],int)

decStaticMethod

                                            int callConv)

The method declaration needs the native variable type of return and parameters and the call convention using the constants declared in CallConv.

The returnType and elements of params follows the same rules as parameters of the constructor declaration of method decConstructor(Class,Object[],int).
